# Sūra XXXVII.: Ṣāffāt, or Those Ranged in Ranks.

### Section 2

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_022.gif)

22. O<u>h</u>shuroo alla<u>th</u>eena *<u>th</u>*alamoo
waazw<u>a</u>jahum wam<u>a</u> k<u>a</u>noo yaAAbudoon**a**

22\. "Bring ye up",  
It shall be said,  
"The wrong-doers  
And their wives,  
And the things they worshipped—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_023.gif)

23. Min dooni All<u>a</u>hi fa**i**hdoohum il<u>a</u>
<u>s</u>ir<u>at</u>i alja<u>h</u>eem**i**

23\. "Besides God,  
And lead them to the Way  
To the (Fierce) Fire!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_024.gif)

24. Waqifoohum innahum masooloon**a**

24\. "But stop them,  
For they must be asked:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_025.gif)

25. M<u>a</u> lakum l<u>a</u> tan<u>as</u>aroon**a**

25\. "What is the matter  
With you that ye  
Help not each other?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_026.gif)

26. Bal humu alyawma mustaslimoon**a**

26\. Nay, but that day they  
Shall submit (to judgment);

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_027.gif)

27. Waaqbala baAA<u>d</u>uhum AAal<u>a</u> baAA<u>d</u>in
yatas<u>a</u>aloon**a**

27\. And they will turn to  
One another, and question  
One [another](errata.htm#5.md).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_028.gif)

28. Q<u>a</u>loo innakum kuntum ta/toonan<u>a</u> AAani alyameen**i**

28\. They will say: "It was ye  
Who used to come to us  
From the right hand  
(Of power and authority)!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_029.gif)

29. Q<u>a</u>loo bal lam takoonoo mu/mineen**a**

29\. They will reply: "Nay, ye  
Yourselves had no Faith!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_030.gif)

30. Wam<u>a</u> k<u>a</u>na lan<u>a</u> AAalaykum min
<u>s</u>ul<u>ta</u>nin bal kuntum qawman <u>ta</u>gheen**a**

30\. "Nor had we any authority  
Over you. Nay, it was  
Ye who were a people  
In obstinate rebellion!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_031.gif)

31. Fa<u>h</u>aqqa AAalayn<u>a</u> qawlu rabbin<u>a</u> inn<u>a</u>
la<u>tha</u>-iqoon**a**

31\. "So now has been proved true,  
Against us, the Word  
Of our Lord that we  
Shall indeed (have to) taste  
(The punishment of our sins).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_032.gif)

32. Faaghwayn<u>a</u>kum inn<u>a</u> kunn<u>a</u> gh<u>a</u>ween**a**

32\. "We led you astray: for truly  
We were ourselves astray."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_033.gif)

33. Fa-innahum yawma-i<u>th</u>in fee alAAa<u>tha</u>bi
mushtarikoon**a**

33\. Truly, that Day, they will  
(All) share in the Penalty.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_034.gif)

34. Inn<u>a</u> ka<u>tha</u>lika nafAAalu bi**a**lmujrimeen**a**

34\. Verily that is how We  
Shall deal with Sinners.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_035.gif)

35. Innahum k<u>a</u>noo i<u>tha</u> qeela lahum l<u>a</u> il<u>a</u>ha
ill<u>a</u> All<u>a</u>hu yastakbiroon**a**

35\. For they, when they were  
Told that there is  
No god except God, would  
Puff themselves up with Pride,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_036.gif)

36. Wayaqooloona a-inn<u>a</u> lat<u>a</u>rikoo <u>a</u>lihatin<u>a</u>
lish<u>a</u>AAirin majnoon**in**

36\. And say: "What! Shall we  
Give up our gods.  
For the sake of  
A Poet possessed?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_037.gif)

37. Bal j<u>a</u>a bi**a**l<u>h</u>aqqi wa<u>s</u>addaqa
almursaleen**a**

37\. Nay! he has come  
With the (very) Truth,  
And he confirms (the Message  
Of) the apostles (before him).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_038.gif)

38. Innakum la<u>tha</u>-iqoo alAAa<u>tha</u>bi al-aleem**i**

38\. Ye shall indeed taste  
Of the Grievous Penalty;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_039.gif)

39. Wam<u>a</u> tujzawna ill<u>a</u> m<u>a</u> kuntum taAAmaloon**a**

39\. But it will be no more  
Than the retribution  
Of (the Evil) that ye  
Have wrought;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_040.gif)

40. Ill<u>a</u> AAib<u>a</u>da All<u>a</u>hi almukhla<u>s</u>een**a**

40\. But the sincere (and devoted)  
Servants of God,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_041.gif)

41. Ol<u>a</u>-ika lahum rizqun maAAloom**un**

41\. For them is a Sustenance  
Determined,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_042.gif)

42. Faw<u>a</u>kihu wahum mukramoon**a**

42\. Fruits (Delights); and they  
(Shall enjoy) honour and dignity,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_043.gif)

43. Fee jann<u>a</u>ti a**l**nnaAAeem**i**

43\. In Gardens of Felicity,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_044.gif)

44. AAal<u>a</u> sururin mutaq<u>a</u>bileen**a**

44\. Facing each other  
On Thrones (of dignity):

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_045.gif)

45. Yu<u>ta</u>fu AAalayhim bika/sin min maAAeen**in**

45\. Round will be passed  
To them a Cup  
From a clear-flowing fountain,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_046.gif)

46. Bay<u>da</u>a la<u>thth</u>atin li**l**shsh<u>a</u>ribeen**a**

46\. Crystal-white, of a taste  
Delicious to those  
Who drink (thereof),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_047.gif)

47. L<u>a</u> feeh<u>a</u> ghawlun wal<u>a</u> hum AAanh<u>a</u>
yunzafoon**a**

47\. Free from headiness;  
Nor will they suffer  
Intoxication therefrom.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_048.gif)

48. WaAAindahum q<u>as</u>ir<u>a</u>tu a**l**<u>tt</u>arfi AAeen**un**

48\. And besides them will be  
Chaste women, restraining  
Their glances, with big eyes  
(Of wonder and beauty).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_049.gif)

49. Kaannahunna bay<u>d</u>un maknoon**un**

49\. As if they were  
(Delicate) eggs closely guarded.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_050.gif)

50. Faaqbala baAA<u>d</u>uhum AAal<u>a</u> baAA<u>d</u>in
yatas<u>a</u>aloon**a**

50\. When they will turn to  
One another and question  
One another.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_051.gif)

51. Q<u>a</u>la q<u>a</u>-ilun minhum innee k<u>a</u>na lee qareen**un**

51\. One of them will start  
The talk and say:  
"I had an intimate  
Companion (on the earth),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_052.gif)

52. Yaqoolu a-innaka lamina almu<u>s</u>addiqeen**a**

52\. "Who used to say,  
"What! art thou amongst those  
Who bear witness to  
The truth (of the Message)?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_053.gif)

53. A-i<u>tha</u> mitn<u>a</u> wakunn<u>a</u> tur<u>a</u>ban
waAAi*<u>th</u>*<u>a</u>man a-inn<u>a</u> lamadeenoon**a**

53\. "When we die and become  
Dust and bones, shall we  
Indeed receive rewards  
And punishments?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_054.gif)

54. Q<u>a</u>la hal antum mu<u>tt</u>aliAAoon**a**

54\. (A voice) said: "Would ye  
Like to look down?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_055.gif)

55. Fa**i**<u>tt</u>alaAAa fara<u>a</u>hu fee saw<u>a</u>-i
alja<u>h</u>eem**i**

55\. He looked down  
And saw him  
In the midst of the Fire.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_056.gif)

56. Q<u>a</u>la ta**A**ll<u>a</u>hi in kidta laturdeen**i**

56\. He said: "By God!  
Thou wast little short  
Of bringing me to perdition!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_057.gif)

57. Walawl<u>a</u> niAAmatu rabbee lakuntu mina almu<u>hd</u>areen**a**

57\. "Had it not been for  
The Grace of my Lord,  
I should certainly have been  
Among those brought (there)!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_058.gif)

58. Afam<u>a</u> na<u>h</u>nu bimayyiteen**a**

58\. "Is it (the case) that  
We shall not die,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_059.gif)

59. Ill<u>a</u> mawtatan<u>a</u> al-ool<u>a</u> wam<u>a</u> na<u>h</u>nu
bimuAAa<u>thth</u>abeen**a**

59\. "Except our first death,  
And that we  
Shall not be punished?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_060.gif)

60. Inna h<u>atha</u> lahuwa alfawzu alAAa*<u>th</u>*eem**u**

60\. Verily this is  
The supreme achievement!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_061.gif)

61. Limithli h<u>atha</u> falyaAAmali alAA<u>a</u>miloon**a**

61\. For the like of this  
Let all strive,  
Who wish to strive.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_062.gif)

62. A<u>tha</u>lika khayrun nuzulan am shajaratu a**l**zzaqqoom**i**

62\. Is that the better entertainment  
Or the Tree of Zaqqūm?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_063.gif)

63. Inn<u>a</u> jaAAaln<u>a</u>h<u>a</u> fitnatan
li**l***<u>thth</u>*<u>a</u>limeen**a**

63\. For We have truly  
Made it (as) a trial  
For the wrong-doers.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_064.gif)

64. Innah<u>a</u> shajaratun takhruju fee a<u>s</u>li
alja<u>h</u>eem**i**

64\. For it is a tree  
That springs out  
Of the bottom of Hell-fire:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_065.gif)

65. <u>T</u>alAAuh<u>a</u> kaannahu ruoosu a**l**shshay<u>at</u>een**i**

65\. The shoots of its fruit-stalks  
Are like the heads  
Of devils:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_066.gif)

66. Fa-innahum la<u>a</u>kiloona minh<u>a</u> fam<u>a</u>li-oona
minh<u>a</u> albu<u>t</u>oon**a**

66\. Truly they will eat thereof  
And fill their bellies therewith.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_067.gif)

67. Thumma inna lahum AAalayh<u>a</u> lashawban min <u>h</u>ameem**in**

67\. Then on top of that  
They will be given  
A mixture made of  
Boiling water.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_068.gif)

68. Thumma inna marjiAAahum la-il<u>a</u> alja<u>h</u>eem**i**

68\. Then shall their return  
Be to the (Blazing) Fire.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_069.gif)

69. Innahum alfaw <u>a</u>b<u>a</u>ahum <u>da</u>lleen**a**

69\. Truly they found their fathers  
On the wrong Path;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_070.gif)

70. Fahum AAal<u>a</u> <u>a</u>th<u>a</u>rihim yuhraAAoon**a**

70\. So they (too) were rushed  
Down on their footsteps!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_071.gif)

71. Walaqad <u>d</u>alla qablahum aktharu al-awwaleen**a**

71\. And truly before them,  
Many of the ancients  
Went astray;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_072.gif)

72. Walaqad arsaln<u>a</u> feehim mun<u>th</u>ireen**a**

72\. But We sent aforetime,  
Among them, (apostles)  
To admonish them;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_073.gif)

73. Fa**o**n*<u>th</u>*ur kayfa k<u>a</u>na AA<u>a</u>qibatu
almun<u>th</u>areen**a**

73\. Then see what was  
The End of those who  
Were admonished (but heeded not),—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/037/037_074.gif)

74. Ill<u>a</u> AAib<u>a</u>da All<u>a</u>hi almukhla<u>s</u>een**a**

74\. Except the sincere (and devoted)  
Servants of God.

